text: Asad Raza (born 25 December 1997) is a Pakistani cricketer. He made his List A debut for Khyber Pakhtunkhwa in the 2017 Pakistan Cup on 25 April 2017. He made his first-class debut for Faisalabad in the 2017–18 Quaid-e-Azam Trophy on 9 October 2017. He made his Twenty20 debut for Faisalabad in the 2017–18 National T20 Cup on 12 November 2017. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Pakistani cricketers Category:Faisalabad cricketers Category:Khyber Pakhtunkhwa cricketers Category:Cricketers from Faisalabad Category:Central Punjab cricketers
